# AI Medical Scribe — Project Overview

## What This Is
A HIPAA-compliant AI medical scribe that records doctor-patient consultations, transcribes them in real-time, and generates structured clinical notes using AI.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- **State**: Zustand (client), TanStack Query (server)
- **Auth & DB**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + RLS + Realtime)
- **AI Pipeline**: Python FastAPI microservices
- **Transcription**: Deepgram Nova-3 Medical (streaming WebSocket)
- **Note Generation**: Claude API (Anthropic)
- **EHR Integration**: FHIR R4 (Epic, Cerner adapters)

## Architecture
```
Browser → Next.js (BFF) → Python AI Services → External APIs
                        → Supabase (data layer)
```

Three Python microservices:
1. **Audio Service** — WebSocket audio streaming → Deepgram transcription
2. **AI Service** — Prompt management + Claude API note generation
3. **EHR Service** — FHIR R4 client for EHR push/pull

## Directory Structure
```
src/
  app/              # Next.js App Router pages
  components/       # React components (ui/, audio/, notes/, layout/)
  hooks/            # Custom React hooks
  lib/              # Utilities, Supabase client, validators
  services/         # Client-side service layer (API calls)
  stores/           # Zustand stores
  types/            # TypeScript type definitions
services/
  ai-pipeline/      # Python FastAPI services
supabase/
  migrations/       # SQL migration files
```

## Key Design Decisions
- Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed (interactivity, hooks)
- All forms validated with Zod schemas (shared between client and server)
- Audio never persists to disk or browser storage — memory only during recording
- All PHI access logged to audit_log table
- WebSocket for real-time audio streaming and transcript updates

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (ConsultationRecorder.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with "use" prefix (useAudioRecorder.ts)
- Utilities: camelCase (formatDuration.ts)
- API routes: kebab-case (/api/generate-note)
- Database: snake_case (clinical_notes)
- Types: PascalCase with descriptive names (ConsultationWithTranscript)
